╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║     AINEX LINE FOLLOWER - COMPLETE COMMAND GUIDE 🚀          ║
╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
STEP 1: BUILD THE WORKSPACE (First Time / After Changes)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

cd ~/competition_ws
catkin build ainex_line_follower

# Expected output: "All packages succeeded!"

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
STEP 2: SOURCE THE WORKSPACE
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

source ~/competition_ws/devel/setup.bash

# Add this to ~/.bashrc for automatic sourcing:
echo "source ~/competition_ws/devel/setup.bash" >> ~/.bashrc

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
STEP 3: LAUNCH THE SIMULATION
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

roslaunch ainex_line_follower line_follower_simulation.launch

# This will:
# ✅ Start Gazebo with line_follower world
# ✅ Spawn the Ainex robot at center (0,0)
# ✅ Start ainex_controller (walking module)
# ✅ Start line_follower node (vision + control)
# ✅ Automatically start walking (after 5 sec delay)

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
STEP 4: MANUALLY START WALKING (If Auto-Start Fails)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# In a NEW terminal:
source ~/competition_ws/devel/setup.bash
rosservice call /walking/command "start"

# You should see robot start walking immediately!

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
OPTIONAL: VIEW DEBUG IMAGE (Recommended!)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# In a NEW terminal:
source ~/competition_ws/devel/setup.bash
rosrun image_view image_view image:=/line_follower_node/debug_image

# This shows:
# • Green ROI box (detection region)
# • Red contour (detected line)
# • Blue dot (line center)
# • Yellow center line
# • Detection status text


1. Open Terminal 1:
   cd ~/competition_ws
   source devel/setup.bash
   roslaunch ainex_line_follower line_follower_simulation.launch

2. Wait 10 seconds for everything to initialize

3. Open Terminal 2:
   source ~/competition_ws/devel/setup.bash
   rosrun image_view image_view image:=/line_follower_node/debug_image

4. Open Terminal 3 (if manual start needed):
   source ~/competition_ws/devel/setup.bash
   rosservice call /walking/command "start"

5. Observe robot following the line!

6. To stop: Ctrl+C in Terminal 
